---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About" description="About Jason Marsh — developer, technologist, assistive technology specialist.">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      I'm Jason — a developer and technologist based in Duluth, Minnesota, with 13+
      years in IT. I direct technology at a nonprofit where I oversee infrastructure,
      assistive technology services, and an AT lending library — serving older
      adults, people with disabilities, and anyone who needs help navigating
      technology. I hold an Assistive Technology Applications
      Certificate from CSUN.
    </p>

    <p>
      Outside of that role, I build things. My projects span recipe intelligence,
      IoT hardware, AI-powered tools, computer vision, and accessible software — all
      shipped solo. My primary stack is Node.js, SQLite, and vanilla JavaScript, with
      Python for machine learning and automation work. Claude is a core part of my
      workflow — not as a crutch but as a building partner.
    </p>

    <p>
      I came to software through art — a B.S. in Game Art & Design, a stint as a
      concept artist doing noir-style western illustrations, and a lot of self-teaching.
      The path was nonlinear, but the throughline is the same: I care about how things
      connect, how they break, and how to make them useful for real people.
    </p>

    <h2>Get in touch</h2>

    <p>
      I'm always interested in conversations about AI engineering, assistive technology,
      or interesting problems. If my work resonates, I'd like to hear from you.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>Email: <a href="mailto:regularlyjason@icloud.com">regularlyjason@icloud.com</a></li>
      <li>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/Minimalistic">Minimalistic</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</Base>
